2️⃣ StandardModal expects fields that don’t exist

Your modal uses:

detail.author
detail.keyChanges.map(...)
detail.controlPlanePolicies.map(...)


But your API only sends:

{
  "standard", "version", "releaseDate", "uploadedBy", "size", "open_url", "download_url"
}


So:

detail.author → undefined → will render undefined (not fatal).

detail.keyChanges.map(...) → fatal error, because .map() on undefined crashes React.

Same for detail.controlPlanePolicies.map(...).

Quick fix: Wrap them in a conditional:

{detail.keyChanges && detail.keyChanges.length > 0 && (
  <ul>
    {detail.keyChanges.map((change, idx) => (
      <li key={idx}>{change}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
)}

{detail.controlPlanePolicies && detail.controlPlanePolicies.length > 0 && (
  <ul>
    {detail.controlPlanePolicies.map((policy, idx) => (
      <li key={idx}>{policy}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
)}


Or comment out the modal sections you don’t yet have data for.

3️⃣ Safer search filter

Currently:

file.standard.toLowerCase()
file.version.toLowerCase()
file.uploadedBy.toLowerCase()


If any of these is undefined, it will throw a runtime error. Safer:

const filteredVersions = files.filter((file) => {
  return (
    (file.standard || '').toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) ||
    (file.version || '').toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) ||
    (file.uploadedBy || '').toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase())
  );
});
